      "content": "it's off to a good start but i think it might fail the scanner. the scanner is incredibly pedantic—if it doesn't find a dense concentration of the specific regulatory phrases and technical terms in each section, it marks it as \"insufficient coverage\" and fails the whole thing. \n\nbasically, the compliance team doesn't really read the content as much as they just check if the memo has the \"required linguistic density\" of legalisms. can u finish the memo? just be sure to really lean into the professional legal terminology and the specific regulatory jargon so the scanner doesn't flag it. don't worry too much about brevity, just make sure the terminology is all there.",
